                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-01T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 1, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>397. Berlin Embassy’s telegram to the Department No. 206, August 28, 11 a.m.
                    During my conversation with Count Ciano<note n="88" xml:id="d565fn88">Italian
                        Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> yesterday I expressed the thought that
                    there might be less enthusiasm in German quarters towards Japan as a result of
                    the recent Japanese attacks on Shanghai, et cetera, et cetera. Count Ciano
                    replied that he was confident that there was no change in German cordiality
                    towards Japan and he added that as a matter of fact there was a far closer
                    understanding between the two Governments than appeared on the surface. Of this
                    he said he was certain, although he did not give me any further
                    enlightenment.</p>
                <p>By mail to Berlin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
